      <h2 class="title">MAHABODHI TEMPLE</h2>
      <p class="desc">
        The Mahabodhi Temple is one of the most sacred Buddhist pilgrimage sites in the world. Located in Bodh Gaya, Bihar, it marks the exact location where **Siddhartha Gautama** attained **enlightenment under the Bodhi Tree**, over 2,500 years ago.
      </p>
      <p class="desc">
        Originally built by **Emperor Ashoka** in the 3rd century BCE, the temple complex is a masterpiece of architecture with a central stupa standing about 55 meters high. It is now a **UNESCO World Heritage Site**, visited by millions of pilgrims and tourists from across the globe.
      </p>
      <p class="desc">
        The sacred **Bodhi Tree**, descendants of the original tree, still stands inside the complex. The site includes monasteries, meditation parks, and peaceful gardens.
      </p>

